
# UI Design Brief (Reconciled)

This brief defines the UI system for the platform using the reconciled module, route, and feature vocabulary.

The UI should feel:
- professional
- premium
- calm
- highly readable
- modular
- expandable

It should support a stable shell and repeatable view patterns rather than page-by-page custom design.

---

# 1. Approved UI Stack

Use:
- Next.js App Router
- shadcn/ui
- Tailwind CSS
- TanStack Table
- React Hook Form
- Zod
- Recharts
- Lucide Icons
- Zustand or React Context

shadcn/ui is the design system foundation.
A custom internal view framework sits on top.

---

# 2. Permanent App Shell

The shell is always present:
- Header
- Sidebar
- Footer

## Header
Contains:
- organization switcher
- global search
- quick create
- notifications
- user menu

## Sidebar
The sidebar is driven by canonical module keys:

- dashboard
- crm_opportunities
- mandates
- research
- results
- companies
- contacts
- integrations
- billing
- settings

The sidebar must not use deprecated module concepts like discovery, shortlist, dossiers, or CRM sync as top-level items.

## Footer
Minimal:
- version
- support/docs
- status

---

# 3. View Framework

Every feature/module must support three base view types:

- inline
- detail
- form

Inline variants:
- table
- cards
- chart
- compact-list

Placements:
- sidebar
- main
- embedded
- modal
- drawer
- hidden

---

# 4. Canonical Module-to-UI Mapping

## dashboard
Overview of the current organization.

## crm_opportunities
Archive of imported CRM records and conversion entry into mandates.

## mandates
Mandate archive and mandate detail.

## research
Research archive and research detail.

## results
Research results archive and result detail inspector.

## companies
Canonical company archive and detail.

## contacts
Canonical contact archive and detail.

## integrations
Provider configuration and connection health.

## billing
Subscription, credits, and billing controls.

## settings
Organization and user/workspace settings.

---

# 5. Reclassified Concepts

These are not top-level modules:

- discovery
- shortlist
- dossiers
- CRM sync
- analytics

They should be rendered as one of:

- embedded views
- result actions
- result detail sections
- export actions
- dashboard widgets
- secondary tabs

### Examples
- shortlist -> results subview / action
- dossiers -> result detail section + export action
- CRM sync -> CRM/mandate/results feature
- analytics -> dashboard widgets or later add-on module if promoted

---

# 6. Mandates UX

When the user clicks Mandates:
- show Mandates Archive
- show + New Mandate

New Mandate options:
- Add manually
- Sync from CRM

Mandate detail shows:
- summary
- files
- linked research runs
- actions:
  - start research
  - edit
  - archive

---

# 7. Research UX

Research is a module.
Strategies are a subview of research.
Results are a separate top-level module.

Research page:
- archive
- status filters
- create/start research

Research detail:
- goal
- rules
- exclusions
- strategies
- status/progress

---

# 8. Results UX

Use the module name **Results** in navigation and routes.

Route:
- /results
- /results/[id]

The results page should use:
- left = result list/table
- right = detail inspector

Detail inspector should read normalized analysis/entity data, not depend on legacy blobs.

Show:
- canonical company/contact summary
- evidence
- psych profile
- fit analysis
- dossier summary
- actions:
  - shortlist
  - export
  - open company
  - open contact

---

# 9. Capability UI Rules

Do not build provider-specific product UI first.

Use capability-first UI actions.

Correct:
- Enrich Contact
- Generate Strategy
- Export Dossier
- Sync CRM

Incorrect:
- Lusha Action
- OpenAI Strategy Button

Provider requirements are resolved underneath through the feature resolver.

---

# 10. Role-Aware UI

## Platform operator roles
- owner
- billing_admin
- developer

These can see:
- integrations
- billing management
- provider/API setup
- module/platform controls

## Workflow roles
- owner
- admin
- manager
- analyst
- member
- developer
- billing_admin (optional visibility)

These can see:
- crm_opportunities
- mandates
- research
- results
- companies
- contacts

The UI should consume resolved feature/module state rather than hardcoding ad hoc role checks in each button.

---

# 11. Source of Truth Rule

Final UI should read:
- companies / company_domains
- contacts / contact_emails / contact_phones
- evidence
- psych_profiles
- lmc_fits
- dossiers

`research_results` legacy JSON fields are transitional only.

---

# 12. Color System

Primary brand color:
- #0F766E
- hover: #115E59
- soft: #CCFBF1
- border accent: #5EEAD4

Accent color:
- #D97706
- hover: #B45309
- soft: #FEF3C7

Use teal as the primary action color.
Use sunburnt yellow only as a restrained accent.
Keep the rest neutral.

---

# 13. Final Direction

Build the product UI as a stable workspace system:
- one fixed shell
- one canonical module list
- one reusable view framework
- capability-first feature actions
- normalized data as source of truth
